problems.description:
Design a distributed cache with cache-aside pattern.

**Cache-Aside (Lazy Loading):**
```java
public User getUser(Long id) {
    // 1. Try cache
    User cached = redis.get("user:" + id, User.class);
    if (cached != null) return cached;
    // 2. Cache miss — load from DB
    User user = userRepo.findById(id).orElseThrow();
    // 3. Populate cache
    redis.set("user:" + id, user, Duration.ofMinutes(30));
    return user;
}

public void updateUser(User user) {
    userRepo.save(user);
    redis.delete("user:" + user.getId()); // invalidate cache
}
```

**Failure modes:**
- Cache miss storm: use `singleflight` or mutex to prevent thundering herd
- Stale data: TTL + invalidation on write
- Cold start: warm cache at startup

**Key insight:** Never update cache and DB in a single 'atomic' operation — they can't be. Delete cache on write; populate lazily on miss.

