public class Q3 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("1. Shard key: user_id (hash-based)");
        System.out.println("   Reason: Colocates all posts for a user on one shard → efficient user feed.");
        System.out.println("   Even distribution: 10M users / N shards = even write load.");
        System.out.println("   Avoids hot spots unless a single user has billions of posts (celebrity problem).");

        System.out.println("\n2. Initial shards: 8-16 (enough to handle current load with headroom)");
        System.out.println("   Growth plan: Use consistent hashing — add shards and migrate only 1/N fraction.");
        System.out.println("   Alternatively: shard into 1024 logical shards, distribute across fewer physical nodes initially;");
        System.out.println("   move logical shards to new physical nodes as needed (no rehashing).");

        System.out.println("\n3. Difficult queries with user_id sharding:");
        System.out.println("   - Global trending posts: must query ALL shards and merge results (scatter-gather)");
        System.out.println("   - Posts by topic/hashtag: no shard affinity → full scatter-gather");
        System.out.println("   - Timeline for followed users: posts on multiple shards → fan-out read");
        System.out.println("   Solution: separate read-optimized store (Elasticsearch, Redis sorted sets) for cross-shard queries");
    }
}
